article.description: — Kellan Grady had a season-high 32 points as Davidson romped past George Mason 99-67 in the quarterfinals of the Atlantic 10 Conference tournament on Friday.
article.headline: Grady scores 32 to lift Davidson past George Mason 99-67
article.linkText: Grady scores 32 to lift Davidson past George Mason 99-67
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- — Kellan Grady had a season-high 32 points as Davidson romped past George Mason 99-67 in the quarterfinals of the Atlantic 10 Conference tournament on Friday. Davidson advanced to face VCU in the semifinals on Saturday. Hyunjung Lee had 20 points for Davidson (13-7). Luka Brajkovic added 17 points. Bates Jones had 11 points. Jordan Miller had 15 points for the Patriots (13-9). Javon Greene added 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
